00:50:14,080 --> 00:50:16,150
- What?
- You know what.

603
00:50:22,000 --> 00:50:24,594
Oh, very good!

604
00:50:24,680 --> 00:50:26,636
Close... yes.

605
00:50:27,840 --> 00:50:29,956
Now...

606
00:50:30,040 --> 00:50:31,792
...Morrison, Senior,

607
00:50:31,880 --> 00:50:35,668
probably the most naturally gifted
golfer of his generation,

608
00:50:35,760 --> 00:50:37,159
addresses the ball.

609
00:50:37,240 --> 00:50:41,233
Slow backswing,
keeping his eye on the ball.

610
00:50:42,600 --> 00:50:44,079
And it's on it's way,

611
00:50:44,160 --> 00:50:46,037
over the humpback bridge,

612
00:50:46,120 --> 00:50:48,509
into the round thing covered in shells,

613
00:50:48,600 --> 00:50:50,636
out the other side...

614
00:50:52,720 --> 00:50:55,632
And it's there!
It's there! Eight under par.

615
00:50:55,720 --> 00:50:58,553
The championship. Well done, Blake.

616
00:50:58,640 --> 00:51:01,359
You did your best,
but at the end of the day,

617
00:51:01,440 --> 00:51:03,749
you were up against a better player.

618
00:51:03,840 --> 00:51:05,637
I enjoyed that.

619
00:51:20,040 --> 00:51:21,837
It would be a lovely hotel to run.

620
00:51:23,880 --> 00:51:26,075
- Do you go camping?
- Oh, here he is.

621
00:51:26,160 --> 00:51:28,674
